label.value: cell sensitive to mechanical stress

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a vegetative cell dies at a level of mechanical stress that wild-type cells can normally withstand.

label.value: normal inositol hexakisphosphate kinase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of inositol hexakisphosphate kinase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased protein localization to CENP-A containing chromatin during mitosis

value.value: A cell phenotype observed during mitotic M phase in which the localization of a protein to CENP-A containing chromatin is decreased.

label.value: decreased glucose import

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of glucose into the cell is decreased with respect to wild-type.

label.value: decreased phenylalanine import during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of phenylalanine into the cell occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: normal growth on glutamate nitrogen source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which cells grow normally (i.e. indistinguishably from wild type) in a medium containing glutamate as the nitrogen source.

label.value: normal growth on glutamine nitrogen source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which cells grow normally (i.e. indistinguishably from wild type) in a medium containing glutamine as the nitrogen source.

label.value: normal growth on arginine nitrogen source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which cells grow normally (i.e. indistinguishably from wild type) in a medium containing arginine as the nitrogen source.

label.value: decreased cell population growth on leucine nitrogen source

value.value: A vegetative cell population phenotype in which cell growth is decreased relative to normal in a medium containing leucine as the nitrogen source.

label.value: decreased cell population growth on alanine nitrogen source

value.value: A vegetative cell population phenotype in which cell growth is decreased relative to normal in a medium containing alanine as the nitrogen source.

label.value: abolished cell population growth on alanine nitrogen source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which a cell population does not grow in a medium containing alanine as the nitrogen source.

definition.value: Use this term for a population of cells that does not grow with alanine as the nitrogen source, but does grow using a different nitrogen source (a cell population that does not grow on any media would be considered inviable). Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: abolished cell population growth on leucine nitrogen source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which a cell population does not grow in a medium containing leucine as the nitrogen source.

definition.value: Use this term for a population of cells that does not grow with leucine as the nitrogen source, but does grow using a different nitrogen source (a cell population that does not grow on any media would be considered inviable). Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: decreased cellular polyphosphate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of polyphosphate measured in a cell (total or free) is lower than normal.

label.value: normal protein localization to CENP-A containing chromatin during mitosis

value.value: A cell phenotype observed during mitotic M-phase in which the localization of a protein to the CENP-A containing chromatin is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased protein localization to CENP-A containing chromatin during mitosis

value.value: A cell phenotype observed during mitotic M-phase in which the localization of a protein to CENP-A containing chromatin is increased.

label.value: increased rate of acid phosphatase activation during phosphate starvation

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate of acid phosphatase activation during phosphate starvation is increased.

label.value: decreased rate of acid phosphatase activation during phosphate starvation

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate of acid phosphatase activation during phosphate starvation is decreased.

label.value: cell lysis during hyphal growth phase

value.value: An inviable phenotype observed during fungal hyphal growth phase in which a cell lyses, i.e. the plasma membrane ruptures and cytoplasm is lost.

label.value: abnormal blue light photoreceptor activity

value.value: A phenotype in which a blue light photoreceptor activity is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal blue light response

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the cellular response to blue light stimulus is abnormal.

label.value: normal mitotic spindle checkpoint activation

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which the mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint activation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: elongated mononucleate aseptate cell with cell cycle arrest in mitotic S-phase

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is elongated, has no septum, and contains one nucleus, and is arrested in mototic S-phase

label.value: normal phosphorylation of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain serine 7 residues during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of the serine residue at position 7 within one or more copies of the heptapeptide repeat (YSPTSPS) of the C-terminal domain of RNA polymerase II normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: ectopic CENP-A containing chromatin assembly at pericentromeric heterochromatin

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin containing the histone H3 variant CenH3 (also called CENP-A; Cnp1 in S. pombe) are assembled in the pericentromeric heterochromatin. CENP-A-containing nucleosomes are normally assembled into chromatin at the centromeres, encompassing the central core and centromeric inner repeat regions.

label.value: increased nucleosome occupancy at CENP-A boundary

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleosome occupancy is higher than normal at the CENP-A boundary. Nucleosome occupancy measures the tendency for DNA in a given region to be packaged into nucleosomes.

label.value: decreased rate of transcription elongation from RNA polymerase II promoter

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate of elongation of a transcript initiated from an RNA polymerase II promoter is abnormal.

label.value: abolished histone H3-K4 trimethylation during mitosis

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in mitosis in which trimethylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 does not occur.

label.value: decreased 1-phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate 5-kinase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a decreased 1-phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate 5-kinase activity is decreased.

label.value: increased cellular phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate level

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: decreased cellular phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate level

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: abolished establishment or maintenance of actin cytoskeleton polarity during vegetative growth

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the establishment or maintenance of actin cytoskeleton polarity is abolished.

label.value: increased protein localization to nucleus during stationary phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is increased during stationary phase.

label.value: swollen elongated multinucleate aseptate vegetative cell with more than four nuclei

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is swollen, elongated, has no septum, and contains more than four nucleus. In a swollen cell, both length and diameter may be greater than normal, although the cell is only considered elongated if the length:diameter ratio is also greater than normal.

definition.value: Multiple nuclear division cycles can cause arrested cells to accumulate up to 32 nuclei.

label.value: elongated vegetative cell with more than four nuclei

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell contains more than four nuclei, is longer than normal, and has a greater length:diameter ratio than normal.

label.value: decreased sexual agglutination in response to blue light

value.value: A cell population phenotype that reflects decreased occurrence of sexual agglutination in response to blue light.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K4 dimethylation  at centromere during meiosis

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in meiosis in which dimethylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 is decreased at the centromere.
We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased histone H3-K4 dimethylation at centromere during meiosis

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in meiosis in which dimethylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 is increased at the centromere.

label.value: increased histone H3-K4 dimethylation during meiosis

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in meiosis in which dimethylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 is increased.

label.value: abolished histone H3-K4 methylation during meiosis

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in meiosis in which dimethylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 is abolished.

label.value: decreased ubiquitin ligase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of ubiquitin ligase activity is decreased.

label.value: increased histone H3-K4 dimethylation during mitosis

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in mitosis in which the dimethylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: decreased intron acceptor binding

definition.value: A molecular function phenotype in which an interaction between a protein and mRNA intron acceptor is decreased. One of the relevant gene products may be encoded by the mutated gene, or both the RNA and protein may be encoded by genes other than the mutated one.

label.value: decreased homocitrate synthase inhibition by L-lysine

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of homocitrate synthase is increased, due to the absence of lysine inhibition.

label.value: decreased Glc2Man9GlcNAc2 oligosaccharide glucosidase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a Glc2Man9GlcNAc2 oligosaccharide glucosidase activity is decreased.

label.value: abolished poly(A)-specific ribonuclease activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which a poly(A)-specific ribonuclease activity is absent.

label.value: abnormal enzyme processivity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed  ability of an enzyme to catalyze consecutive reactions without releasing the substrate (i.e. template) is abnormal.

label.value: increased polyA ribonuclease processivity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed  ability of a polyA robonuclease to catalyze consecutive reactions without releasing the substrate (i.e. template) is abnormal.

label.value: decreased K48-linked polyubiquitin binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the binding of a protein to K48-linked polyubiquitin occurs to a lower extent than normal.

definition.value: This term can be used for any protein-protein interaction that is affected by a mutation, whether or not the mutated gene product is one of the interacting proteins. We recommend noting which proteins were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal mono ubiquitin binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the binding of one protein to a ubiquitin monomer is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: This term can be used for any protein-protein interaction that is tested in a mutant, whether or not the mutated gene product is one of the interacting proteins. We recommend noting which proteins were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished phosphorylation of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain serine 5 residues during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of the serine residue at position 5 within one or more copies of the heptapeptide repeat (YSPTSPS) of the C-terminal domain of RNA polymerase II does not occur.
